cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a method for whole brain segmentation using 3D Fully Convolutional Neural Networks (F-CNNs) and focuses on model compression through ternary quantization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method and compares it with various baselines, indicating a focus on machine learning and optimization, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely categories. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, indicating cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with volumetric data, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as a possible category.
